      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak the fruit overnight",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put {{sultanas}}, {{currants}}, {{raisins}}, and {{light-brown-sugar}} in a large bowl. Pour over 350 ml of cold strong black tea. Stir, cover, and leave overnight at room temperature, the fruit will absorb most of the liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C (140°C fan). Line a 900 g (2 lb) loaf tin with baking paper. Beat the {{eggs}} into the soaked fruit, then stir in {{self-raising-flour}} and {{mixed-spice}} until just combined. The batter will be thick and sticky. Scrape into the tin, smooth the top, and bake for 55 to 65 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. The top should be dark brown and firm. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes before turning out. Leave to cool completely before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
